# zKCNT POS Project Conventions

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: Nuxt 3 (Vue 3) with Tailwind CSS v4, SSR disabled (SPA/PWA)
- Local DB: Dexie.js (IndexedDB wrapper)
- Backend: PocketBase v0.38 (SQLite-backed, single binary)
- Containerization: Docker with separate dev/prod compose files

## Architecture: Offline-First + Multi-Tenant

### Multi-Tenant Pattern
- Every business data collection MUST have a `store` relation field
- All queries MUST filter by the active store ID
- PocketBase API rules MUST verify store membership via `store_members`
- Dexie compound indexes: `[store+field]` for store-scoped queries

### Offline-First Pattern
- All reads go through Dexie.js (local cache) first
- Online writes: PocketBase first, then sync to Dexie
- Offline writes: write to Dexie + add to `syncQueue`
- On reconnect: drain sync queue, then pull remote changes
- Conflict resolution: last-write-wins using `updated` timestamp

